  "prompt": "Which are the most romantic movies?",
  "response": "Romantic movies have a special place in the hearts of many, as they explore themes of love, passion, and connection. Here\u2019s a list of some of the most beloved and romantic films across different eras and styles:\n\n### **Classic Romantic Movies**\n1. **Casablanca** (1942) - A timeless tale of love and sacrifice set during World War II.\n2. **Gone with the Wind** (1939) - A sweeping epic of love and resilience during the Civil War.\n3. **Roman Holiday** (1953) - A charming story of a princess and a reporter falling in love in Rome.\n4. **An Affair to Remember** (1957) - A tearjerker about two lovers who plan to reunite at the Empire State Building.\n5. **The Notebook** (2004) - A modern classic about enduring love and memory.\n\n### **Modern Romantic Movies**\n1. **La La Land** (2016) - A musical love story with dreamy visuals and a bittersweet ending.\n2. **The Fault in Our Stars** (2014) - A touching story of two teenagers with cancer who fall in love.\n3. **Call Me by Your Name** (2017) - A beautifully shot film about first love and self-discovery.\n4. **A Star is Born** (2018) - A heartbreaking love story between a musician and a rising star.\n5. **Crazy, Stupid, Love** (2011) - A romantic comedy with multiple intertwining love stories.\n\n### **Romantic Comedies**\n1. **When Harry Met Sally** (1989) - A witty exploration of friendship turning into love.\n2. **Pretty Woman** (1990) - A modern Cinderella story with Julia Roberts and Richard Gere.\n3. **10 Things I Hate About You** (1999) - A high school romantic comedy based on Shakespeare\u2019s *The Taming of the Shrew*.\n4. **Love Actually** (2003) - A feel-good ensemble film about various forms of love during the holidays.\n5. **Notting Hill** (1999) - A sweet story about a bookstore owner falling for a famous actress.\n\n### **International Romantic Movies**\n1. **Am\u00e9lie** (2001) - A whimsical French film about a shy woman who orchestrates love for others while finding her own.\n2. **Cinema Paradiso** (1988) - An Italian masterpiece about friendship, love, and the magic of cinema.\n3. **In the Mood for Love** (2000) - A visually stunning Hong Kong film about unspoken love and longing.\n4. **Like Water for Chocolate** (1992) - A Mexican film blending romance, magic, and food.\n5. **The Lunchbox** (2013) - An Indian romance about two strangers connecting through misplaced letters.\n\n### **Fantasy/Sci-Fi Romances**\n1. **The Princess Bride** (1987) - A fairy tale romance filled with adventure and humor.\n2. **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind** (2004) - A unique story about love, memory, and second chances.\n3. **Stardust** (2007) - A magical adventure with a sweet romantic core.\n4. **About Time** (2013) - A heartwarming tale of love and time travel.\n5. **The Shape of Water** (2017) - A fairy-tale romance between a mute woman and a mysterious aquatic creature.\n\nThese films offer a wide range of romantic experiences, from classic tales of love to unconventional and modern stories. Whether you\u2019re in the mood for laughter, tears, or a bit of both, there\u2019s a romantic movie for everyone!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
